Feature Elimination

  1. There are attributes that can be deleted which do not contirbute in the prediction
  2. CustomerId, Surname, RowNumber attributes can be removed the data frame
  3. Extract the Exixted attribute to y for the prediction

y = df['Exited']

  1. Looking at the geography attribute majority of the customers are from France
  2. Churning of female is customer is proportinate to male customers.
  3. Inactive members churn rate is high. Bank has to implement measures to convert them to active.

Encode categoriacal variables

Gender and Geography attributes need to be encoded. Let's use LabelEncoder for this process

In [17]:
gender_encoder = LabelEncoder()
X['Gender'] = gender_encoder.fit_transform(X['Gender'])
In [18]:
geography_encoder = LabelEncoder()
X['Geography'] = geography_encoder.fit_transform(X['Geography'])
X = pd.get_dummies(X, drop_first=True, columns=['Geography'])

Model Building

In [23]:
model = Sequential()
model.add(Dense(X.shape[1], activation='relu', input_dim = X.shape[1]))
model.add(Dense(32, activation='relu'))
model.add(Dense(1, activation = 'sigmoid'))

Compile model with Optimzier and loss function

In [24]:
sgd = optimizers.Adam(lr = 0.001)
In [25]:
